Description: A cream-coloured ostrich eggshell bead, oval in shape. A hole was drilled from the exterior to the interior through the centre of the bead. Tool marks are visible around the edge of the bead.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Bir Kiseiba, E-79-6 Gebal el Feel Playa
Bibliographic references: Wendorf, Schild & Close 1984 / Cattle-Keepers of the Eastern Sahara The Neolithic of Bir Kiseiba (p. 212, fig. 10.10, a)
Additional IDs: Excavation/small finds number: E101E1 (2nd excavation number)
